  "texts": [
    "Motivation.",
    "Did you motivate your actions?",
    "To have higher Agency, we motivate our intentions through reasoning and evidence.",
    "Without such motivation, intentions are simply ideas, often lacking the capability to cause a change.",
    "We characterize strong motivation as providing evidence in support of one's preference (e.g., \"I think a blue-colored chair will complement the wall\"), moderate motivation as agreeing with another person's preference and providing evidence in their favor (e.g., \"I agree."
  ]
